@kipkuch Hi there, I can't reproduce this on my Win 7 Professional SP1 laptop.

Did you previously have another version of CouchDB installed first? Did you completely remove that version if so?

Did you install CouchDB to a path **without** spaces, such as `C:\CouchDB`? The installer warns that CouchDB won't work right if you install to a path with spaces such as `C:\Program Files\CouchDB`.

@ermouth if tests are possible, that'd be great, otherwise this might break again (esp. if others are not familiar with the code).

Otherwise I'll rebase this later tonight.

@kxepal nice to see you, and thanks!

@janl How is `httpsd` enabled in this new world? Previously that would have been:

```
[daemons]
httpsd = {chttpd, start_link, [https]}
```

@JohnOllhorn The person in that ticket seems happy with that solution - why not try it?

Use what works best for you. We are a volunteer project here. Our volunteers who do cluster things prefer to use Kubernetes, and they are very successful with it. Why not give it a try?

Our feelings won't be hurt if you switch to MongoDB.

